WEBVTT

00:03.291 --> 00:05.083
♪ OHHH OHHH OHHH ♪

00:07.250 --> 00:11.417
(indistinct conversations)

00:11.458 --> 00:14.083
(knock on door)

00:14.125 --> 00:17.041
COOPER, GET OUT.

00:17.083 --> 00:19.041
OH, YOU LOOK INCREDIBLE.

00:19.083 --> 00:21.333
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO SEE ME YET.

00:21.375 --> 00:23.041
I THINK...

00:23.083 --> 00:26.000
I-I THINK IT'S A MISTAKE
FOR US TO DO THIS.

00:29.166 --> 00:31.458
(elevator bell dings)

00:31.500 --> 00:34.500
(indistinct conversations)

00:37.458 --> 00:40.041
(exhales deeply)

00:40.083 --> 00:42.667
HEY. YOU OKAY?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

00:42.709 --> 00:45.041
ARE YOU
WORRIED ABOUT SOMETHING?

00:45.083 --> 00:47.041
ARE YOU GETTING
PRE-WEDDING JITTERS?

00:47.083 --> 00:49.875
YOU GONNA JILT COOPER
AT THE ALTAR?

00:49.917 --> 00:51.875
BECAUSE I WILL DRIVE
THE GETAWAY VEHICLE,

00:51.917 --> 00:53.917
NO QUESTIONS ASKED.
I AM NOT JILTING, COOP.

00:53.959 --> 00:56.917
IT'S JUST, WEDDINGS MEAN FAMILY,
AND OUR FAMILIES...

00:56.959 --> 01:00.041
(sighs) LOOK, MY MAMA IS
A STRAIGHT-UP SOUTHERN BELLE,

01:00.083 --> 01:02.041
WHICH MEANS
SHE'S CHARMING, JUDGMENTAL,

01:02.083 --> 01:04.041
AND NOT AFRAID
TO SELF-MEDICATE.

01:04.083 --> 01:05.041
(chuckles)

01:05.083 --> 01:07.041
IMAGINING HER
WITH THE FREEDMANS...

01:07.083 --> 01:09.000
AND IF THEY'RE ANYTHING LIKE
THEIR SON,

01:09.041 --> 01:11.000
THEY'LL WANT TO HUG HER
AND KISS HER

01:11.041 --> 01:14.000
AND WHINE ABOUT HOW THERE AREN'T
ANY GOOD DELIS IN LOS ANGELES.

01:14.041 --> 01:16.083
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES
WHEN YOU HAVE THOSE

01:16.125 --> 01:19.083
"WORLDS COLLIDE" SITUATIONS,
THEY ACTUALLY TURN OUT OKAY.
AND SOMETIMES THEY END
WITH A GIANT FIREBALL

01:19.125 --> 01:20.917
THAT CONSUMES
EVERYTHING AROUND 'EM.

01:20.959 --> 01:22.917
WELL, HOW MUCH TIME DO THEY
HAVE TO SPEND TOGETHER

01:22.959 --> 01:24.291
BEFORE THE WEDDING?

01:24.333 --> 01:26.959
(sighs) COOPER AND I THOUGHT
WE COULD LIMIT IT TO A DINNER.

01:27.000 --> 01:28.959
IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO TO HELP?

01:29.000 --> 01:30.542
PLAN THE DINNER.

01:30.583 --> 01:34.083
OH. OKAY. UH, I WAS REALLY
JUST ASKING TO BE POLITE,

01:34.125 --> 01:37.041
BUT YOU REALLY WANT ME
TO DO IT?

01:37.083 --> 01:39.750
I JUST FIGURED, IF YOU'RE
GONNA BE MY MAID OF HONOR...

01:39.792 --> 01:42.041
WAIT. WHAT? REALLY? ME?

01:42.083 --> 01:45.083
WE'RE JUNKIES TOGETHER. THAT
MAKES US B.F.F.s IN MY BOOK.

01:45.125 --> 01:47.917
AND COOPER HAS VIOLET
AS HIS BEST MAN.

01:47.959 --> 01:50.875
HE KEEPS SAYING I NEED SOMEONE
TO STAND UP WITH ME,

01:50.917 --> 01:53.875
SO I WOULD VERY MUCH LIKE YOU
TO BE MY MAID OF HONOR.

01:53.917 --> 01:57.291
JUST DON'T FORGET TO BRING
YOUR FIRE EXTINGUISHER.

01:59.709 --> 02:03.041
(footsteps approach)

02:03.083 --> 02:05.041
(knocks on door)

02:05.083 --> 02:08.000
CAN I HELP YOU?
I'M DR. VIOLET TURNER.

02:08.041 --> 02:11.041
I WAS TOLD YOU WERE THE MEDICAL
INVESTIGATOR ON MY CASE.

02:11.083 --> 02:13.542
DID WE HAVE AN APPOINTMENT
FOR TODAY?

02:13.583 --> 02:15.875
NO. NO, I JUST... I THOUGHT
WE COULD TAKE A FEW MOMENTS

02:15.917 --> 02:17.875
TO TALK ABOUT KATIE KENT.

02:17.917 --> 02:20.875
DR. TURNER--
I MEAN, THIS WHOLE THING HAS
BEEN BLOWN OUT OF PROPORTION,

02:20.917 --> 02:24.250
AND I-I WANTED TO TELL MY SIDE
OF THE STORY, AND YOU'LL SEE--

02:24.291 --> 02:26.917
I-I THINK WE CAN AVOID
WASTING EVERYONE'S TIME

02:26.959 --> 02:28.917
ON ANY KIND
OF FORMAL INVESTIGATION.

02:28.959 --> 02:31.750
WE HAVE A PROTOCOL,
AND I'M OBLIGATED TO FOLLOW IT.

02:31.792 --> 02:34.208
PLEASE HEAR ME OUT.

02:34.250 --> 02:38.041
AS LONG AS YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT WHATEVER YOU TELL ME

02:38.083 --> 02:40.417
WILL IN NO WAY
LIMIT THE INVESTIGATION

02:40.458 --> 02:43.208
WE'VE ALREADY OPENED
INTO YOUR CASE

02:43.250 --> 02:45.000
AND CAN ALSO BE USED

02:45.041 --> 02:47.041
AS THE BASIS
FOR FURTHER INQUIRIES.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.500
(opens drawer)

02:49.542 --> 02:51.000
(clicks button)

02:53.000 --> 02:55.125
READY WHEN YOU ARE.

03:05.709 --> 03:09.458
(people speaking indistinctly)

03:09.500 --> 03:11.875
HEY.

03:11.917 --> 03:14.458
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE BACK.

03:14.500 --> 03:16.875
UH, HOW WAS AFRICA?

03:16.917 --> 03:19.041
IT WAS GOOD.
IT WAS REALLY GOOD.

03:19.083 --> 03:21.125
YEAH? YOU LOOK AMAZING.
ARE YOU--

03:21.166 --> 03:23.125
I'M--I'M--I'M LATE
FOR A MEETING. HI.

03:23.166 --> 03:25.333
HEY. WELCOME BACK,
NA--
YEAH.

03:25.375 --> 03:27.667
OMI.
SHE HATES ME.

03:27.709 --> 03:29.667
WELL, SHE'S NOT TOO CRAZY
ABOUT ME, EITHER.

03:29.709 --> 03:32.041
SO, UH...

03:32.083 --> 03:34.583
ARE WE STILL AGREED?

03:34.625 --> 03:36.583
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
KEEP ASKING ME THAT.

03:36.625 --> 03:38.875
WELL, I JUST DON'T WANT
THINGS TO BE AWKWARD

03:38.917 --> 03:41.500
FOR CHARLOTTE AND COOPER.
IT'S NOT GONNA BE,
ALL RIGHT?

03:41.542 --> 03:43.500
WE'RE NOT GONNA TELL ANYBODY
WE'RE BROKEN UP.

03:43.542 --> 03:45.500
WE'RE GONNA GO
TO THE WEDDING TOGETHER,

03:45.542 --> 03:48.709
AND THEN AFTERWARDS, WE'RE
GONNA TELL EVERYBODY THAT--
WE'RE STILL FRIENDS. OKAY.

03:48.750 --> 03:51.166
(Addison pours liquid)

03:51.208 --> 03:53.291
(knock on door)

03:53.333 --> 03:55.458
YOU'RE GONNA GET A CALL
FROM THE MEDICAL BOARD

03:55.500 --> 03:57.041
INVESTIGATING VIOLET.

03:57.083 --> 03:59.250
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S THIS SERIOUS.

03:59.291 --> 04:02.041
WELL, BELIEVE.
THEY'RE GONNA INTERVIEW YOU.
ME?

04:02.083 --> 04:04.041
YOU AND I ARE THE ONLY OTHER
DOCTORS WHO TREATED KATIE,

04:04.083 --> 04:06.792
AND I JUST GOT MY CALL, SO...
YOU REALLY THINK

04:06.834 --> 04:09.834
THERE'S A CHANCE
SHE COULD LOSE HER LICENSE?
YES.

04:09.875 --> 04:12.208
BUT IF WE CAN HELP EXPLAIN
WHAT HAPPENED...

04:12.250 --> 04:15.250
JUST BE VERY CAREFUL
WHEN YOU ANSWER THEIR QUESTIONS.

04:15.291 --> 04:18.125
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT ASKING ME
TO LIE.

04:18.166 --> 04:20.125
I'M ASKING YOU
TO PROTECT VIOLET.

04:20.166 --> 04:22.125
I DON'T NEED
TO BE PROTECTED.

04:22.166 --> 04:24.417
ALL THE THERAPY
I DID WITH KATIE,

04:24.458 --> 04:27.041
THE--THE ATTACK, THE TRIAL,
THE BOOK--

04:27.083 --> 04:29.041
I HAVE NOTHING TO HIDE,

04:29.083 --> 04:31.083
AND NEITHER DO YOU.

04:38.542 --> 04:40.041
(motor whirs)

04:40.083 --> 04:42.041
MISS ME?

04:42.083 --> 04:43.917
(gasps) GABRIEL,
WHAT ARE YOU--

04:43.959 --> 04:45.917
I HEARD YOUR SPEECH,
BUT I AM CONFIDENT

04:45.959 --> 04:48.041
THAT EVENTUALLY, YOU WILL
SEE THE ERROR OF YOUR WAYS,

04:48.083 --> 04:50.792
AND WHEN YOU DO,
I'LL BE HERE, WAITING.

04:50.834 --> 04:52.166
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

04:52.208 --> 04:54.166
I HAVE A PATIENT
IN ASSISTED LIVING.

04:54.208 --> 04:57.083
I'M MAKING A HOUSE CALL.

04:57.125 --> 04:59.083
THERE ARE LAWS
AGAINST STALKING.

04:59.125 --> 05:02.041
OH, PRISON DOESN'T SCARE ME.

05:02.083 --> 05:03.458
(door opens)

05:03.500 --> 05:05.166
(Naomi) MARION?

05:05.208 --> 05:08.000
(motor whirs)

05:08.041 --> 05:09.917
MARION?

05:09.959 --> 05:12.583
HI. DID I FORGET
TO TELL YOU THAT I WAS COMING?

05:12.625 --> 05:15.375
OH, I'M SURE YOU DIDN'T.

05:15.417 --> 05:17.333
UH, THIS IS DR. FIFE.

05:17.375 --> 05:20.583
HE'S A COLLEAGUE OF MINE.

05:20.625 --> 05:22.625
WHY DON'T WE GIVE MARION
A-A MINUTE?

05:22.667 --> 05:24.709
I'VE NEVER SEEN HER
IN ANYTHING OTHER THAN A DRESS

05:24.750 --> 05:28.041
WITH HER HAIR AND NAILS DONE,
WHICH MEANS SHE'S BEING POLITE.

05:28.083 --> 05:29.792
WOULDN'T HAVE MATTERED.

05:32.458 --> 05:34.041
IS THIS YOU?

05:34.083 --> 05:36.041
YES, AND MY HUSBAND JEROME.

05:36.083 --> 05:37.917
HOW LONG WERE YOU MARRIED?

05:37.959 --> 05:42.041
JEROME DIED JUST BEFORE
OUR 51st ANNIVERSARY.
(beeps)

05:42.083 --> 05:45.291
WELL, BET YOU CAN STILL
FIT IN THAT DRESS.

05:45.333 --> 05:48.625
MARION, YOUR GLUCOSE
IS REALLY HIGH.

05:48.667 --> 05:51.041
HAVE YOU BEEN TAKING
YOUR INSULIN?
(motor whirs, thuds)

05:51.083 --> 05:52.583
OH, CAREFUL.

05:52.625 --> 05:54.208
IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG?

05:54.250 --> 05:56.041
OH.

05:56.083 --> 05:59.041
YOU'RE NOT YOURSELF TODAY,
MARION. DID SOMETHING HAPPEN?

05:59.083 --> 06:02.041
IF YOU WANT TO TALK,
DR. FIFE CAN LEAVE AND--

06:02.083 --> 06:03.583
OH, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

06:05.375 --> 06:07.041
YOU KNOW, MARION,

06:07.083 --> 06:09.041
THERE IS A THERAPIST
HERE ON STAFF.

06:09.083 --> 06:11.166
AND I HAVE TWO IN MY OFFICE.

06:11.208 --> 06:13.583
YOU WANT ME TO TALK
TO SO-SOME STRANGER

06:13.625 --> 06:15.041
HALF MY AGE,

06:15.083 --> 06:16.834
TELL 'EM I'M SAD,

06:16.875 --> 06:18.834
AND THEN LISTEN TO HIM
TRY TO PUT THINGS

06:18.875 --> 06:20.875
IN A PERSPECTIVE
HE DOESN'T HAVE?

06:20.917 --> 06:23.041
I-I-IT'S JUST, THAT IF
YOU'RE REALLY SAD, THEN--

06:23.083 --> 06:24.875
WE CAN ZAP THE SADNESS OUT.

06:24.917 --> 06:28.375
THERE'S A PROCEDURE CALLED
AN ANTERIOR CINGULOTOMY.

06:28.417 --> 06:30.709
THE NEUROSURGEON USES
A GAMMA KNIFE

06:30.750 --> 06:33.083
TO DESTROY THE PARTS OF
THE BRAIN THAT CAUSE DEPRESSION.

06:33.125 --> 06:34.917
GABRIEL.

06:34.959 --> 06:36.917
OH. LISTEN, THANK YOU BOTH
FOR COMING HERE.

06:36.959 --> 06:40.041
I'LL TRY TO REMEMBER
THE INSULIN.

06:40.083 --> 06:42.041
BUT I DON'T NEED SHRINKS

06:42.083 --> 06:43.709
AND I DON'T NEED KNIVES.

06:43.750 --> 06:46.834
I JUST NEED TO BE LEFT ALONE.

06:51.417 --> 06:53.041
(Violet) OH.

06:53.083 --> 06:55.041
HEY, COOPER,
UH, THIS IS, UH,

06:55.083 --> 06:57.166
THIS IS MY LAWYER,
RICHARD HUVANE.
HELLO.

06:57.208 --> 06:59.375
YOU WENT TO SPEAK WITH
NEAL CHAPLIN WITHOUT ME PRESENT?

06:59.417 --> 07:02.417
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?
I WAS THINKING THAT IF KATIE
HAS DROPPED THE LAWSUIT,

07:02.458 --> 07:05.041
THERE'S NO REASON FOR
THE MEDICAL BOARD TO PURSUE IT.
BUT THEY ARE PURSUING IT.

07:05.083 --> 07:07.041
AND NOW THAT THEY'VE OPENED
AN INVESTIGATION,

07:07.083 --> 07:09.500
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT SHE DOES.

07:09.542 --> 07:11.500
WELL, I...
I-I-I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

07:11.542 --> 07:13.500
AS SOON AS HE BROUGHT OUT
THE RECORDER, I LEFT.

07:13.542 --> 07:15.834
I'M GONNA CATCH UP
TO YOU LATER, OKAY?

07:15.875 --> 07:18.917
LOOK, I-I WAS JUST THINKING
THAT IF I COULD...

07:18.959 --> 07:21.834
(sighs) I TALKED TO PETE
ABOUT IT--

07:21.875 --> 07:24.083
PETE IS NOW A WITNESS
IN THIS INVESTIGATION.

07:24.125 --> 07:26.875
ARE--ARE YOU SAYING
I NEED TO BE CAUTIOUS

07:26.917 --> 07:28.417
AROUND MY OWN HUSBAND?

07:28.458 --> 07:31.208
YOU NEED TO BE CAUTIOUS
AROUND EVERYONE.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.542
IT'S YOUR LICENSE
THAT'S ON THE LINE.

07:42.166 --> 07:45.041
THE WOMAN IS PROBABLY JUST
DEPRESSED, AND FIFE SUGGESTS

07:45.083 --> 07:47.917
DESTROYING PART OF HER BRAIN.
WELL, IF YOU INVITED HIM,
YOU SHOULD'VE KNOWN.

07:47.959 --> 07:50.458
I DID NOT INVITE HIM.
IT'S PART OF MY STRATEGY.

07:50.500 --> 07:52.667
I DID AN ANTERIOR CINGULOTOMY
BACK AT HOPKINS.

07:52.709 --> 07:55.333
PRE-OP, THE MAN WOULD NOT
EVEN GET OUT OF BED.

07:55.375 --> 07:58.041
POST-OP, HE WAS COOKING DINNER
FOR THE ENTIRE NEIGHBORHOOD.

07:58.083 --> 08:00.083
WE GAVE HIM HIS LIFE BACK.
SO THERE.

08:00.125 --> 08:02.041
BUT ANY SURGERY
ON SOMEONE MARION'S AGE

08:02.083 --> 08:04.458
IS GONNA BE RIFE
WITH POTENTIAL COMPLICATIONS,

08:04.500 --> 08:07.458
INCLUDING A STROKE--
WELL, YOU HAVE TO BE
BRAVE ENOUGH TO TAKE THAT RISK.

08:07.500 --> 08:10.041
ACTUALLY, YOU'RE ASKING
THE PATIENT TO TAKE THAT RISK,

08:10.083 --> 08:12.041
WHICH I'M NOT SURE
MAKES YOU BRAVE AT ALL.

08:12.083 --> 08:14.041
MORE IMPORTANTLY, MARION HAS
ALREADY MADE IT CLEAR

08:14.083 --> 08:17.208
THAT SHE DOES NOT WANT
THIS SURGERY.
THAT'S THE DEPRESSION TALKING.

08:17.250 --> 08:18.834
IT'S CLOUDING HER JUDGMENT

08:18.875 --> 08:20.834
AND MAKING HER INCAPABLE
OF AN INFORMED DECISION.

08:20.875 --> 08:22.834
DEPRESSION DOESN'T NECESSARILY
MAKE SOMEONE INCOMPETENT.

08:22.875 --> 08:24.333
UNLESS IT DOES,

08:24.375 --> 08:26.291
WHICH MAKES THIS
KIND OF A CATCH-22.

08:26.333 --> 08:28.125
I MEAN, WE CAN'T TREAT
HER DEPRESSION

08:28.166 --> 08:30.542
IF HER DEPRESSION IS PREVENTING
HER FROM SEEKING TREATMENT.

08:30.583 --> 08:33.709
MARION SHOULDN'T BE
INCLUDED IN THIS.
WHAT?

08:33.750 --> 08:37.041
THE DISEASE DETERMINES
THE CURE, NOT THE PATIENT.
LISTENING TO YOUR PATIENT,
WORKING WITH THEM,

08:37.083 --> 08:39.208
THAT'S ESSENTIAL
TO GOOD DOCTORING.

08:39.250 --> 08:41.667
HEALING IS ESSENTIAL
TO GOOD DOCTORING.

08:41.709 --> 08:44.250
AMELIA USES THE GAMMA KNIFE,
MARION WILL FEEL BETTER.

08:44.291 --> 08:46.959
IT'S A WIN-WIN.
NO ONE IS DOING
ANY KIND OF CUTTING

08:47.000 --> 08:48.959
UNTIL WE DETERMINE
JUST HOW BAD OFF MARION IS.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.625
WILL YOU PLEASE
TALK TO HER?

08:51.667 --> 08:53.250
SURE.

08:53.291 --> 08:55.333
THANK YOU.

08:55.375 --> 08:57.959
WHAT A LOVELY PLACE
TO WORK.

08:58.000 --> 09:00.041
AND, UH, SAVING THE BEST
FOR LAST--

09:00.083 --> 09:02.417
THIS IS THE OFFICE
OF DR. CHARLOTTE KING.

09:02.458 --> 09:05.625
(laughter)

09:05.667 --> 09:08.250
(man) VIOLET,
YOU ARE FUNNY AS EVER.

09:08.291 --> 09:10.333
OH.
WHOO-HOO.

09:10.375 --> 09:13.333
(woman claps hands)
MOM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

09:13.375 --> 09:15.458
OOH.
HI. (laughs)

09:15.500 --> 09:18.875
YOU TOLD US TO WAIT,
BUT YOU KNOW YOUR MOTHER.

09:18.917 --> 09:21.208
WE WERE TOO EXCITED,
SO WE CAME ON OVER.

09:21.250 --> 09:23.208
AND THEN WE SAW VIOLET
IN THE ELEVATOR...

09:23.250 --> 09:27.041
WHO HAS THIS AMAZING FIGURE,
EVEN AFTER HAVING A BABY.
(Cooper) YEAH, YEAH.

09:27.083 --> 09:32.041
YEAH, I WAS JUST COMING
TO FIND YOU.
UH, MOM, DAD,

09:32.083 --> 09:34.375
UM, THIS IS CHARLOTTE,
AND THIS IS HER MOTHER,

09:34.417 --> 09:36.583
AUGUSTA KING.

09:36.625 --> 09:38.792
IT'S A PLEASURE.
HELLO.

09:38.834 --> 09:40.875
HELLO.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

09:49.083 --> 09:53.333
WELL, ISN'T THIS GREAT,
EVERYBODY FINALLY MEETING?

09:53.375 --> 09:55.291
(chuckles)

09:55.333 --> 09:58.083
HEY, MAYBE I'LL JUST SHOW MAMA
AROUND THE REST OF THE OFFICE.

09:58.125 --> 10:01.041
OH, GREAT IDEA. UM, WHY DON'T
YOU GUYS COME WITH US? GO WITH--

10:01.083 --> 10:03.333
ACTUALLY, YOU KNOW, YOUR MOTHER
AND I ARE KIND OF HUNGRY.

10:03.375 --> 10:05.458
(Violet) OH, WELL, IT'S--
IT'S LUNCH TIME RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

10:05.500 --> 10:08.083
WHY DON'T YOU ALL GO
TO THE PROMENADE

10:08.125 --> 10:10.625
AND HAVE LUNCH FIRST?
(woman) THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.
AND YOU'LL BE JOINING US, RIGHT?

10:10.667 --> 10:14.041
OH, WELL, I'M--I'M REALLY
KIND OF BUSY.
OF COURSE SHE'S COMING
WITH US.

10:14.083 --> 10:16.667
CHARLOTTE, I'D LOVE TO SEE
YOUR OFFICE. NOW.

10:16.709 --> 10:18.959
OH, BUT LET'S, UH...
UH, LUNCH?

10:19.000 --> 10:21.041
ANOTHER TIME.

10:21.083 --> 10:22.959
ENJOY.

10:23.000 --> 10:26.041
(man) WELL, I'M THINKING DELI,
BUT, UH,

10:26.083 --> 10:29.041
I COULD BE PERSUADED TO TRY
SOMETHING A LITTLE MORE RISQUE.

10:29.083 --> 10:30.792
(footsteps approach)

10:30.834 --> 10:32.792
(knock on door)
(Addison) HEY.

10:32.834 --> 10:34.792
I KEEP RUNNING INTO FIFE
IN THE HALLS.

10:34.834 --> 10:37.291
IS HE, UH, WORKING HERE
AGAIN OR--

10:37.333 --> 10:40.875
NO, HE JUST--HE SAYS HE WON'T GO
AWAY UNTIL I AGREE TO DATE HIM.

10:40.917 --> 10:42.250
WOW.

10:42.291 --> 10:46.250
I GIVE HIM A 10
FOR PERSEVERANCE.

10:46.291 --> 10:48.917
SO WHAT DO YOU RATE HIM
FOR STYLE?

10:48.959 --> 10:50.500
YOU KNOW WHAT?

10:50.542 --> 10:53.458
I HAVE A BUNCH OF RESEARCH
I HAVE TO DO, SO...

10:53.500 --> 10:56.291
OH. OKAY.

10:56.333 --> 10:57.750
OKAY.

11:00.083 --> 11:03.917
HEY, SAM AND I BROKE UP.
I, UH...

11:03.959 --> 11:06.041
I JUST THOUGHT
YOU SHOULD KNOW.

11:10.333 --> 11:11.709
WHY?

11:11.750 --> 11:14.500
WELL, HE WOULDN'T COMMIT
TO HAVING A CHILD WITH ME

11:14.542 --> 11:16.500
AND I DIDN'T WANT TO WAIT--

11:16.542 --> 11:18.583
NO, I MEANT WHY--WHY ARE YOU
TELLING ME THIS?

11:18.625 --> 11:20.166
I MEAN, Y--

11:20.208 --> 11:22.709
YOU AND I,
WE'RE NOT EXACTLY...

11:22.750 --> 11:25.625
LOOK, NAI, THERE'S BEEN
THIS WALL UP BETWEEN YOU AND ME

11:25.667 --> 11:27.625
SINCE SAM AND I GOT TOGETHER,

11:27.667 --> 11:29.667
AND I DON'T
WANT IT THERE ANYMORE.

11:29.709 --> 11:31.709
I WANT MY BEST FRIEND BACK.

11:37.083 --> 11:40.875
THAT'S IT?
YOU'RE NOT GONNA SAY ANYTHING?

11:42.291 --> 11:44.625
I HOPE IT WAS WORTH IT.

11:47.291 --> 11:50.583
I TOLD YOU, YOU SHOULD'VE
ORDERED THE BRISKET.

11:50.625 --> 11:54.041
(laughs) I'M SORRY. IT'S JUST,
UM, JUST KIND OF A BAD DAY.

11:54.083 --> 11:57.333
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?
I-I THINK I SHOULD GO.

11:57.375 --> 11:59.000
WHAT, SO SOON?

11:59.041 --> 12:01.333
DAD, ENOUGH. LET HER GO.

12:01.375 --> 12:04.375
WELL, THE THREE OF YOU
NEED TIME TO CATCH UP,

12:04.417 --> 12:08.667
AND, UM, YEAH, I'LL SEE YOU
BACK AT THE OFFICE.
FINE.

12:10.125 --> 12:12.250
IS EVERYTHING OKAY
WITH VIOLET?

12:12.291 --> 12:14.875
I SWEAR, SHE DIDN'T SMILE ONCE
THE WHOLE MEAL.

12:14.917 --> 12:17.041
SHE IS... GOING THROUGH
A ROUGH PATCH RIGHT NOW.

12:17.083 --> 12:18.875
SHE'LL BE OKAY.

12:18.917 --> 12:20.917
WELL, I HOPE SO.
SHE IS SUCH A GOOD GIRL.

12:20.959 --> 12:22.917
IS THERE ANYTHING
THAT WE CAN DO TO HELP?

12:22.959 --> 12:25.166
YEAH, HOW ABOUT WORRYING
A LITTLE LESS ABOUT VIOLET

12:25.208 --> 12:28.166
AND ASKING ME
ABOUT MY FUTURE WIFE?
WELL, WE INTRODUCED OURSELVES,

12:28.208 --> 12:31.667
AND THEN SHE AND HER MOTHER
WERE GONE.
ARE YOU REALLY SURPRISED?

12:31.709 --> 12:34.041
I MEAN, YOU COMPLETELY SHUT DOWN
WHEN I INTRODUCED YOU.

12:34.083 --> 12:36.917
WELL, THE MOTHER
WAS PLEASANT ENOUGH.

12:36.959 --> 12:41.041
BUT I DID FIND CHARLOTTE
TO BE A BIT... COLD.

12:41.083 --> 12:43.750
CHARLOTTE IS NOT COLD. IT TAKES
A WHILE TO GET TO KNOW HER.

12:43.792 --> 12:45.333
WE KNOW ENOUGH.

12:45.375 --> 12:48.875
OH, YEAH? WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

12:48.917 --> 12:51.250
COOPER,
FOR THE LAST FEW YEARS,

12:51.291 --> 12:53.250
YOUR FATHER AND I
HAVE LISTENED TO YOU--

12:53.291 --> 12:56.041
EVERY PHONE CALL,
EVERY E-MAIL.

12:56.083 --> 12:59.250
AND DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY
OF THOSE WERE YOU BEING UPSET

12:59.291 --> 13:01.875
ABOUT SOMETHING CHARLOTTE DID?
COME ON. WAIT A MINUTE.
THAT IS NOT FAIR.

13:01.917 --> 13:04.875
NO, SHE'S RIGHT, COOP. WE WENT
THROUGH ALL OF THAT WITH YOU--

13:04.917 --> 13:07.959
THE LYING TO THE EX-HUSBAND,
SLEEPING WITH THAT ARTHUR--

13:08.000 --> 13:10.041
ARCHER.
(woman) OH, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

13:10.083 --> 13:12.041
THE POINT IS, SHE'S HURT YOU,
MORE THAN ONCE.

13:12.083 --> 13:15.041
AND WE--WE UNDERSTAND THAT
YOU'RE GOING TO MARRY HER, BUT--

13:15.083 --> 13:17.041
BUT YOU CAN UNDERSTAND
WHY WE CAN'T EXACTLY

13:17.083 --> 13:20.166
OPEN OUR ARMS TO HER AND PRETEND
THAT NOTHING HAPPENED.

13:20.208 --> 13:22.000
YOU'RE--YOU'RE MY PARENTS.

13:22.041 --> 13:24.000
I WAS GIVING YOU ONE SIDE
OF THE STORY.

13:24.041 --> 13:26.041
THERE'S LOTS OF GOOD STUFF
ABOUT CHARLOTTE

13:26.083 --> 13:29.041
THAT I DIDN'T TELL YOU.
WELL, I'M SURE THAT'S TRUE,
BUT WE LOVE YOU, COOPER,

13:29.083 --> 13:31.041
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

13:31.083 --> 13:34.542
SO ANYONE WHO HURTS YOU...

13:34.583 --> 13:36.375
MM.

13:36.417 --> 13:39.500
(indistinct conversations)

13:39.542 --> 13:41.500
(Charlotte) THE CHUPPAH
WILL BE OVER HERE.

13:41.542 --> 13:43.542
UH, THAT'S JUST
A LITTLE GAZEBO.

13:43.583 --> 13:46.083
I KNOW WHAT A CHUPPAH IS,
DARLING.

13:46.125 --> 13:48.500
IT'S THE ONE CONCESSION
COOPER ASKED FOR.

13:48.542 --> 13:50.291
IT'S IMPORTANT
FOR HIS PARENTS.

13:50.333 --> 13:52.041
OH, HIS PARENTS.

13:52.083 --> 13:54.041
YOU KNOW, CHARLOTTE,

13:54.083 --> 13:57.208
THE FREEDMANS
AREN'T THOSE HUGGY, KISSY,

13:57.250 --> 14:00.792
IN-YOUR-FACE KIND OF PEOPLE
YOU WARNED ME ABOUT.

14:00.834 --> 14:02.709
IN FACT,
THEY'RE A LITTLE COLD.

14:02.750 --> 14:05.291
YOU'RE RIGHT.
THEY WERE COLD.

14:05.333 --> 14:07.917
AND THE WAY THEY FAWNED
OVER THAT OTHER DOCTOR--

14:07.959 --> 14:10.083
WHAT'S HER NAME?
VIOLET.

14:10.125 --> 14:13.208
YOU WOULD THINK SHE WAS
THE ONE MARRYING COOPER.

14:13.250 --> 14:15.208
COOPER AND VIOLET
ARE BEST FRIENDS.

14:15.250 --> 14:17.250
HIS PARENTS HAVE KNOWN HER
FOR A LONG TIME.

14:17.291 --> 14:18.875
(laughs) BEST FRIENDS?

14:18.917 --> 14:20.875
I SUGGEST YOU DO AS I DO

14:20.917 --> 14:23.875
AND TRY NOT TO LET THAT
GET UNDER YOUR SKIN.

14:23.917 --> 14:25.250
YOU LISTEN, BABY GIRL,

14:25.291 --> 14:28.208
AS YOUR MOTHER, I HAVE TO
TELL YOU HOW IT IS,

14:28.250 --> 14:30.208
AND HIS PARENTS
DO NOT LIKE YOU.

14:30.250 --> 14:33.875
THEY BARELY KNOW ME.
HONEY, THEY'RE NOT LOOKING
TO KNOW YOU.

14:33.917 --> 14:35.041
MAMA.

14:35.083 --> 14:37.041
NO, LOOK...

14:37.083 --> 14:39.875
I BET THEY'RE OUT THERE
RIGHT NOW WITH COOPER

14:39.917 --> 14:43.875
TELLING HIM THAT YOU ARE NOT
HIS KIND OF GIRL.
I HIGHLY DOUBT THAT.

14:43.917 --> 14:46.041
I'M NOT SAYING
COOPER'S GONNA LISTEN.

14:46.083 --> 14:50.083
I'M JUST SAYING, YOU MARRY
A BOY, YOU MARRY HIS FAMILY.

14:50.125 --> 14:53.041
JUST CONSIDER IT A WARNING.
I CAN'T
TALK ABOUT THIS ANYMORE.

14:53.083 --> 14:55.041
I HAVE TO GET
TO MY FINAL DRESS FITTING.

14:55.083 --> 14:58.041
OH, I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE IT ON YOU. (laughs)

14:58.083 --> 15:00.250
I'M NOT DOING ANYTHING.

15:00.291 --> 15:02.792
LOOK, MAMA, YOU CAN COME
TO THE FITTING,

15:02.834 --> 15:05.583
BUT THE DRESS... IT'S NOT
GONNA MAKE YOU HAPPY.

15:05.625 --> 15:08.041
DID SOMETHING HAPPEN TO IT
IN THE MAIL?

15:08.083 --> 15:10.041
NO, IT ARRIVED JUST FINE,

15:10.083 --> 15:14.041
BUT... I'M NOT WEARING
THE FAMILY DRESS.

15:14.083 --> 15:15.417
CHARLOTTE...

15:15.458 --> 15:18.291
FOR A HUNDRED YEARS,
THE WOMEN IN OUR FAMILY

15:18.333 --> 15:21.417
HAVE WORN THAT DRESS
WHEN THEY TOOK THEIR VOWS.

15:21.458 --> 15:23.041
IS THIS BECAUSE OF COOPER?

15:23.083 --> 15:25.458
HAS HE TALKED YOU OUT
OF WEARING THAT DRESS?

15:25.500 --> 15:27.458
COOPER DOESN'T KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT THE DRESS.

15:27.500 --> 15:29.125
NOW LISTEN TO ME, MAMA.

15:29.166 --> 15:31.125
I WORE THE DRESS
WHEN I MARRIED BILLY,

15:31.166 --> 15:33.458
AND LOOK WHERE THAT GOT ME.

15:33.500 --> 15:36.875
(scoffs) THAT CAN'T POSSIBLY BE
THE DRESS' FAULT.

15:36.917 --> 15:39.250
NOW I KNOW YOU DON'T WANT
TO DO THIS,

15:39.291 --> 15:41.458
BUT IT'S WHAT BIG DADDY
WOULD'VE WANTED.

15:41.500 --> 15:44.250
AND I KNOW YOU DON'T WANT
TO LET HIM DOWN.

15:48.000 --> 15:51.500
(sighs) DR. BENNETT
SHOULD LEAVE WELL ENOUGH ALONE.

15:51.542 --> 15:53.959
WELL, DR. BENNETT DOESN'T FEEL
YOU ARE WELL ENOUGH.

15:54.000 --> 15:55.959
THAT'S WHY SHE ASKED ME
TO TALK TO YOU.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.458
SHE'S CONCERNED
THAT YOU MIGHT BE DEPRESSED.

15:58.500 --> 16:01.041
SHE SAID SHE OFFERED YOU
SEVERAL TREATMENT OPTIONS,

16:01.083 --> 16:04.083
BUT YOU DIDN'T SEEM
TO HAVE ANY INTEREST.
WELL, THAT'S MY RIGHT,
ISN'T IT?

16:04.125 --> 16:06.709
YES, BUT OUR GOAL
IS TO MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER.

16:06.750 --> 16:08.709
AND IT'S POSSIBLE
THAT YOUR ILLNESS

16:08.750 --> 16:10.166
IS STANDING IN THE WAY

16:10.208 --> 16:13.166
OF YOUR ABILITY TO DISCERN
WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU.

16:13.208 --> 16:16.750
DR. WALLACE,
ONE DAY YOU'LL BE OLD.

16:16.792 --> 16:20.166
YOU'LL BE OLD AND THEN
EVENTUALLY YOU'LL BE SICK.

16:20.208 --> 16:23.875
AND THEN YOU'LL BE SAD...
AND LONELY.

16:23.917 --> 16:26.875
AND SOMETIMES, YOU WON'T WANT
TO GET OUT OF BED

16:26.917 --> 16:29.041
OR BE WITH PEOPLE.

16:29.083 --> 16:32.291
WHEN THAT HAPPENS, I HOPE NOBODY
TREATS YOU LIKE A CHILD,

16:32.333 --> 16:35.834
BECAUSE IT ONLY MAKES YOU
FEEL WORSE.

16:42.083 --> 16:44.041
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU WANT TO AVOID ME,

16:44.083 --> 16:46.041
YOU SHOULD KNOW BETTER
THAN TO COME IN HERE

16:46.083 --> 16:48.041
WHEN I'M HAVING
MY PRE-DINNER BREAKFAST.

16:48.083 --> 16:51.041
OH. I'M NOT TRYING
TO AVOID YOU.

16:51.083 --> 16:52.583
I'M NOT.

16:52.625 --> 16:54.583
I JUST, UH...

16:54.625 --> 16:58.125
IT'S JUST, THE REENTRY
GETS HARDER EVERY TIME.

16:58.166 --> 17:00.500
(laughs)

17:00.542 --> 17:03.458
YOU KNOW, I MISS MAYA AND OLIVIA
SO MUCH WHEN I'M GONE.

17:03.500 --> 17:06.125
BUT WHEN I'M TRAVELING
FOR THE FOUNDATION,

17:06.166 --> 17:08.959
I JUST--I-I HAVE A PURPOSE.

17:09.000 --> 17:11.333
YOU KNOW, THE WORK WE DO,
IT'S CHANGING LIVES,

17:11.375 --> 17:14.041
AND I SEE IT.
I SEE IT EVERY DAY.

17:14.083 --> 17:17.542
THEN I COME BACK HERE
TO ALL THE... PETTY DRAMA.

17:17.583 --> 17:20.458
(laughs) WE'RE PRETTY
WELL-STOCKED IN THAT.

17:20.500 --> 17:23.041
YEAH. I'M SORRY.

17:23.083 --> 17:25.542
I-I DIDN'T MEAN TO DOWNPLAY
WHAT HAPPENED

17:25.583 --> 17:28.250
WITH YOU AND ADDISON.

17:30.291 --> 17:33.041
SHE TOLD YOU.

17:33.083 --> 17:34.750
UNBELIEVABLE.

17:34.792 --> 17:37.208
WHAT, WAS I NOT SUPPOSED
TO KNOW?

17:37.250 --> 17:40.250
WELL, WE, UH, WE HAD AGREED
NOT TO TELL ANYBODY

17:40.291 --> 17:41.875
UNTIL AFTER THE WEDDING,

17:41.917 --> 17:43.875
BUT STILL,
SHE GOES RUNNING TO YOU.

17:43.917 --> 17:47.208
YOU KNOW, THAT'S JUST...
THAT'S WHO SHE IS.

17:47.250 --> 17:49.166
IT'S WHO SHE'S ALWAYS BEEN.

17:49.208 --> 17:52.083
WELL, HOW DO YOU--
HOW DO YOU GET PAST THAT?

17:53.750 --> 17:55.959
I DON'T THINK YOU CAN.

18:03.417 --> 18:04.875
SO YOU TREATED MS. KENT
FOR PAIN?

18:04.917 --> 18:07.000
NOT JUST PAIN. SHE HAD NAUSEA
ASSOCIATED WITH HER PREGNANCY.

18:07.041 --> 18:08.375
DID YOU
PRESCRIBE HER ANYTHING?

18:08.417 --> 18:10.041
I TOOK A HOLISTIC APPROACH--

18:10.083 --> 18:12.542
ACUPUNCTURE, ACUPRESSURE.

18:12.583 --> 18:15.500
WERE YOU AT ALL CONCERNED
ABOUT HOW SHE WAS RESPONDING?

18:15.542 --> 18:17.500
SPECIFICALLY,
DO YOU FEEL LIKE MS. KENT

18:17.542 --> 18:19.291
WAS GETTING BETTER OR WORSE?

18:19.333 --> 18:22.834
AFTER SHE MISCARRIED, I NEEDED
TO PERFORM AN EMERGENCY D&amp;C.

18:22.875 --> 18:24.291
DID YOU
PERFORM IT IMMEDIATELY?

18:24.333 --> 18:26.291
NO, NOT IMMEDIATELY.

18:26.333 --> 18:28.417
WHY NOT?

18:28.458 --> 18:30.875
ANSWER THE QUESTION, PLEASE.

18:30.917 --> 18:33.250
VIOLET, UH...
(clears throat)

18:33.291 --> 18:35.458
DR. TURNER
FELT IT WAS IMPORTANT

18:35.500 --> 18:38.041
THAT KATIE FULLY COMPREHEND
THE LOSS OF HER BABY

18:38.083 --> 18:40.083
BEFORE THE PROCEDURE.

18:40.125 --> 18:43.917
AND WHAT HAPPENED
AS A RESULT OF THE DELAY?

18:43.959 --> 18:47.291
KATIE WENT INTO SEPTIC SHOCK.

18:47.333 --> 18:50.250
BUT SHE CAME THROUGH
JUST FINE.

18:50.291 --> 18:53.709
AND YOU BELIEVE IT WAS MEDICALLY
APPROPRIATE TO HAVE WAITED?

18:53.750 --> 18:55.125
YES, KATIE WAS--

18:55.166 --> 18:57.083
I... UM,
VIOLET CALMED HER DOWN,

18:57.125 --> 18:59.667
AND THEN I DID THE D&amp;C.

18:59.709 --> 19:02.083
AND HOW DID DR. TURNER
CALM HER DOWN?

19:02.125 --> 19:04.083
SHE RELATED THE EXPERIENCES
OF HER OWN PREGNANCY.

19:04.125 --> 19:06.709
IT WAS A WAY OF BONDING,
AND IT WORKED.

19:06.750 --> 19:09.041
AND HOW EXACTLY DO YOU KNOW
WHAT WAS SAID

19:09.083 --> 19:11.041
DURING KATIE'S THERAPY SESSION
WITH DR. TURNER?

19:11.083 --> 19:13.583
UH, I DON'T KNOW SPECIFICS,

19:13.625 --> 19:15.875
BUT OUR PRACTICE
IS COOPERATIVE.

19:15.917 --> 19:19.041
DOCTORS OFTEN DISCUSS
THEIR CASES WITH EACH OTHER.

19:19.083 --> 19:20.917
INCLUDING MATTERS NOT RELEVANT

19:20.959 --> 19:22.917
TO THEIR SPECIFIC AREAS
OF RESPONSIBILITY

19:22.959 --> 19:24.417
TO THOSE PATIENTS?

19:24.458 --> 19:26.417
IS THAT REALLY THE ETHIC
OF YOUR PRACTICE?

19:26.458 --> 19:28.417
WELL, NOW YOU'RE MAKING US
SOUND LIKE GOSSIPS.

19:28.458 --> 19:30.750
THEN LET ME CLARIFY
MY QUESTION.

19:30.792 --> 19:33.041
DOES DR. TURNER EVER SHARE
THE PERSONAL DETAILS

19:33.083 --> 19:34.709
OF HER PATIENTS WITH YOU,

19:34.750 --> 19:37.041
EVEN WHEN
YOU'RE NOT TREATING THEM?

19:37.083 --> 19:40.208
ONLY WHEN IT'S THERAPEUTICALLY
BENEFICIAL TO THE PATIENT.

19:40.250 --> 19:43.208
CAN YOU PLEASE LIST THE NAMES
OF ALL OTHER PATIENTS

19:43.250 --> 19:45.834
WITH WHOM DR. TURNER SHARED
SUCH PERSONAL INFORMATION?

19:45.875 --> 19:47.875
(pen thuds)

19:53.000 --> 19:54.959
SO YOU GOT NOWHERE?

19:55.000 --> 19:56.542
ON THE CONTRARY.

19:56.583 --> 19:59.041
AN HOUR IN THE LOBBY
WAS VERY INFORMATIVE.

19:59.083 --> 20:01.250
IT'S LIKE A COLLEGE DORM
FOR SEPTUAGENARIANS.

20:01.291 --> 20:03.041
EVERYONE INTO EVERYONE
ELSE'S BUSINESS.

20:03.083 --> 20:04.625
NOT UNLIKE THIS PRACTICE.

20:04.667 --> 20:08.041
(sighs) I ASKED AROUND. MARION
HAD A GOOD FRIEND NAMED WALTER.

20:08.083 --> 20:10.333
HE DIED OF A HEART ATTACK
A FEW WEEKS AGO.
WELL, SO MAYBE THAT'S IT.

20:10.375 --> 20:13.041
THAT'S WHY SHE'S BEEN GIVING UP
AND NOT TAKING CARE OF HERSELF.

20:13.083 --> 20:17.041
SHE'S JUST GRIEVING.
MM-HMM. SHE IS.
BUT WHEN YOU GET TO HER AGE,

20:17.083 --> 20:19.041
LOSS IS
A MUCH MORE COMMON OCCURRENCE.

20:19.083 --> 20:22.041
AND I THINK THE BEST WAY
TO DEAL WITH IT IS THERAPY.

20:22.083 --> 20:24.875
MM. MOST ELDERLY PATIENTS
ARE RESISTANT

20:24.917 --> 20:27.667
TO THE STANDARD TREATMENT
OF MEDS AND TALK THERAPY.

20:27.709 --> 20:30.458
AND FRANKLY, AT MARION'S AGE,
SHE DOESN'T HAVE THE LUXURY

20:30.500 --> 20:32.458
OF SPENDING FIVE YEARS
ON YOUR COUCH,

20:32.500 --> 20:35.041
ESPECIALLY WHEN ALL HER PAIN
CAN BE ERADICATED

20:35.083 --> 20:36.458
WITH ONE PROCEDURE.

20:36.500 --> 20:38.458
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS
ON YOUR PSYCHIATRIC DEGREE.

20:38.500 --> 20:40.458
WHERE--WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?
OH, SNARK AWAY.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.834
PRETTY SOON, YOU'LL BE ABLE
TO GET ONE OUT OF A CEREAL BOX.

20:42.875 --> 20:44.458
WITH THE ADVENT
OF PSYCHOSURGERIES

20:44.500 --> 20:46.458
AND NEW
PSYCOPHARMACEUTICALS,

20:46.500 --> 20:48.917
YOUR DEGREE
IS BECOMING OBSOLETE.
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

20:48.959 --> 20:51.500
YOU DON'T EVEN WORK
FOR THE PRACTICE ANYMORE.
OH, I'M HERE FOR HER.

20:51.542 --> 20:54.583
OKAY, TH-THIS
IS NOT PRODUCTIVE.
NO, IT ISN'T,
BUT YOU'RE BEING MYOPIC.

20:54.625 --> 20:57.041
THE BEST THING FOR MARION
IS THE GAMMA KNIFE SURGERY.

20:57.083 --> 20:59.875
WELL, SHE DOESN'T AGREE,
AND NEITHER DO I.

21:01.458 --> 21:03.083
(Matt Duncan)
♪ KICKING A BOTTLE ♪

21:03.125 --> 21:05.250
♪ DOWN AN EMPTY STREET ♪

21:05.291 --> 21:08.041
♪ WHERE THE TREES GROW TALL ♪

21:08.083 --> 21:10.041
♪ AND THE OLD FOLKS SLEEP ♪

21:10.083 --> 21:13.083
♪ WE WALKED LONG
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG ♪

21:13.125 --> 21:15.041
IT CAN'T BE THAT BAD.

21:15.083 --> 21:17.041
(Charlotte) I'M NOT
SHOWING IT TO YOU.

21:17.083 --> 21:19.041
COME ON. YOU LOOK AMAZING
IN EVERYTHING.

21:19.083 --> 21:21.041
UGH. NOT THIS.

21:21.083 --> 21:22.417
♪ ...A SUNNY DAY ♪

21:22.458 --> 21:25.625
♪ YOU CAN BE DONE WITH IT
AND WALK AWAY ♪

21:25.667 --> 21:29.041
(laughs) WH--

21:29.083 --> 21:32.125
OH. WHOA.
SEE? IT'S AWFUL.

21:32.166 --> 21:34.125
IT WAS AWFUL
THE FIRST TIME AROUND.

21:34.166 --> 21:35.750
IT'S AWFUL NOW.

21:35.792 --> 21:38.041
HOW CAN SHE EXPECT ME
TO WEAR THIS THING AGAIN?

21:38.083 --> 21:40.333
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TELL HER NO?

21:40.375 --> 21:43.166
'CAUSE IN MY FAMILY,
WE'RE NOT RUDE.

21:43.208 --> 21:44.959
♪ COUNTING OUR BLESSINGS ♪

21:45.000 --> 21:47.458
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

21:47.500 --> 21:49.041
YOU DESCRIBED YOUR PARENTS

21:49.083 --> 21:52.041
AS THESE UNBELIEVABLY WARM,
CARING PEOPLE.

21:52.083 --> 21:55.041
IT WAS ALL THEY COULD DO
TO SHAKE MY HAND.

21:55.083 --> 21:59.166
WELL, YEAH,
THEY WERE A LITTLE, UH...

21:59.208 --> 22:01.458
THEY'RE SENSITIVE
TO OUR HISTORY.

22:01.500 --> 22:04.333
OUR HISTORY?
COME ON, CHARLOTTE.

22:04.375 --> 22:06.917
YOU HURT ME A FEW TIMES,
AND I-I-I TALKED TO THEM--

22:06.959 --> 22:09.083
I SEE YOU HUDDLIN'
IN THE BEDROOM ON THE PHONE,

22:09.125 --> 22:12.083
AND I KNOW WHO YOU'RE
TALKING TO, BUT I JUST ASSUMED

22:12.125 --> 22:15.166
YOU WEREN'T SHARING THE INTIMATE
DETAILS OF OUR RELATIONSHIP.

22:15.208 --> 22:17.625
YOU'RE A GROWN-ASS MAN.

22:17.667 --> 22:19.709
I'M SORRY I DON'T HAVE
AN EMOTIONALLY STUNTED PARENT

22:19.750 --> 22:23.041
TO TAKE AFTER.
JUST BECAUSE WE DON'T VOMIT
OUR EMOTIONS ALL OVER EACH OTHER

22:23.083 --> 22:25.625
EVERY TWO SECONDS DOESN'T MEAN
WE'RE ANY LESS FEELING.

22:25.667 --> 22:28.625
NO? WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT
IT DOES MEAN?

22:28.667 --> 22:30.625
♪ YOU CAN BE DONE WITH IT ♪

22:30.667 --> 22:33.375
LET'S STOP THIS.
TOO LATE.

22:33.417 --> 22:35.750
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU SHOULD WEAR THAT DRESS.

22:35.792 --> 22:38.041
IT LOOKS GREAT ON YOU.
SCREW YOU.

22:38.083 --> 22:41.709
♪ ...ON YOUR ARM ♪

22:45.709 --> 22:48.709
(Amos Lee's "Violin" playing)

22:53.083 --> 22:55.750
(sighs) I TALKED TO
THE MEDICAL INVESTIGATOR.

22:55.792 --> 22:57.333
IT DIDN'T GO WELL.

22:57.375 --> 23:00.041
I MEAN, I ANSWERED EVERYTHING
AS WELL AS I COULD,

23:00.083 --> 23:02.875
BUT I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE--
MAYBE I SAID TOO MUCH.

23:02.917 --> 23:05.041
WELL, THAT WOULDN'T BE
A FIRST.

23:05.083 --> 23:07.834
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

23:07.875 --> 23:09.834
YOU TOLD NAOMI ABOUT US.

23:09.875 --> 23:13.041
THE SAME DAY WE DECIDED
TO KEEP OUR SPLIT A SECRET,

23:13.083 --> 23:14.792
YOU WENT AND TOLD HER.

23:14.834 --> 23:18.083
SHE HAD
A RIGHT TO KNOW, SAM.
NO, THIS DIDN'T INVOLVE HER.

23:18.125 --> 23:20.792
WELL, SHE'S YOUR EX-WIFE
AND MY BEST FRIEND,

23:20.834 --> 23:22.500
SO IT DID INVOLVE HER.

23:22.542 --> 23:24.500
PLEASE. YOU JUST WANTED
TO BE LET OFF THE HOOK.

23:24.542 --> 23:27.041
WHAT DID YOU THINK,
THAT IF YOU TOLD HER FIRST,

23:27.083 --> 23:30.041
SHE'D FORGIVE YOU
FOR EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED?
THAT'S NOT FAIR, SAM.

23:30.083 --> 23:32.291
NO, BUT IT'S TRUE.

23:32.333 --> 23:34.458
MAYA, NAOMI, AND I
ADJUSTED OUR LIVES TO

23:34.500 --> 23:37.458
ACCOMMODATE THIS RELATIONSHIP,
AND YOU CAN'T SEE THAT.

23:37.500 --> 23:40.250
YOU CAN'T ACKNOWLEDGE
THE TOLL THAT TOOK.

23:40.291 --> 23:42.834
IT TOOK
A TOLL ON ME, TOO, SAM.

23:42.875 --> 23:45.041
I MEAN, I SACRIFICED
MY BEST FRIEND

23:45.083 --> 23:48.041
FOR A MAN I WAS SURE I WAS
GONNA RAISE A FAMILY WITH.

23:48.083 --> 23:50.667
YOU THINK I'M BEING SELFISH?
TAKE A LOOK AT YOURSELF.

23:50.709 --> 23:53.208
YOU'VE WANTED ME
SINCE MED SCHOOL, OKAY?

23:53.250 --> 23:54.875
SO DON'T FLATTER YOURSELF

23:54.917 --> 23:57.875
THAT ANY PAIN THAT THIS
HAS CAUSED IS ALL MY FAULT.

23:57.917 --> 24:00.750
THIS RELATIONSHIP DIDN'T
JUST HAPPEN. YOU WENT AFTER IT.

24:00.792 --> 24:02.667
♪ PULL ME THROUGH ♪

24:02.709 --> 24:05.250
YOU'RE RIGHT.

24:05.291 --> 24:07.333
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,
ADDISON?

24:07.375 --> 24:10.583
MAYBE WE CAN'T BE FRIENDS.

24:13.792 --> 24:15.542
♪ LATELY I ♪

24:15.583 --> 24:17.959
♪ AND LATELY I ♪

24:18.000 --> 24:20.333
DING, DING.
WEDDING UPDATE.

24:20.375 --> 24:23.083
YOU WILL BE EXCITED TO KNOW
THAT IN BETWEEN ARRANGING

24:23.125 --> 24:26.083
WHAT IS GOING TO BE
A RIDICULOUSLY DELICIOUS SPREAD

24:26.125 --> 24:27.959
FOR YOUR DINNER,

24:28.000 --> 24:29.959
I HAVE ALSO PURCHASED
AN AMAZING DRESS

24:30.000 --> 24:31.458
FOR THE WEDDING.

24:31.500 --> 24:34.458
BUT IT'S NOT WHITE
AND IT'S NOT VERA WANG.

24:34.500 --> 24:39.041
I PROMISE, EVERYONE
WILL BE FOCUSED ON YOU.

24:39.083 --> 24:41.375
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU
ABOUT THE DRESS.

24:41.417 --> 24:43.959
THEN WHY THE LOOK?

24:44.000 --> 24:45.333
♪ USING WORDS AS AMMUNITION ♪

24:45.375 --> 24:47.041
COOPER'S PARENTS
DON'T LIKE ME.

24:47.083 --> 24:49.125
THEY JUST MET YOU.

24:49.166 --> 24:51.041
HE POISONED THEM.

24:51.083 --> 24:53.750
WHAT? WHY?

24:53.792 --> 24:55.750
I DON'T THINK HE MEANT TO,

24:55.792 --> 24:57.750
BUT APPARENTLY,
HE TELLS THEM EVERYTHING,

24:57.792 --> 24:59.750
INCLUDING EVERY MISTAKE
I'VE EVER MADE.

24:59.792 --> 25:01.583
THEY CAN BARELY LOOK AT ME.

25:01.625 --> 25:04.125
WELL, HAVE YOU CONFRONTED THEM
ABOUT IT?

25:04.166 --> 25:06.083
WHAT AM I GONNA SAY,

25:06.125 --> 25:08.709
"SORRY I DID ALL THESE
TERRIBLE THINGS TO YOUR SON,

25:08.750 --> 25:10.709
BUT PLEASE ACCEPT ME,
LOVE ME"?

25:10.750 --> 25:12.709
WELL, CAN'T COOPER
CONVINCE THEM?

25:12.750 --> 25:15.208
I THINK COOPER'S DONE
ENOUGH DAMAGE.

25:15.250 --> 25:17.583
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

25:17.625 --> 25:20.000
(sighs) HOPE WE MAKE IT
TO THE ALTAR

25:20.041 --> 25:22.041
BEFORE THEY
CONVINCE HIM OTHERWISE.

25:22.083 --> 25:25.375
♪ PULL ME THROUGH ♪

25:27.917 --> 25:30.417
(Amelia) NO, YOU CAN'T.

25:30.458 --> 25:32.542
(Neal) LADIES,
PLEASE STEP ASIDE.

25:32.583 --> 25:34.667
YOU'RE NOT TAKING
OUR FILES.

25:34.709 --> 25:37.250
WE'RE NOT TAKING THEM.
WE'RE ONLY COPYING THEM.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

25:37.291 --> 25:40.041
THEY'RE TRYING TO TAKE
OUR PATIENT FILES.
THEY'RE RELEVANT
TO OUR INVESTIGATION.

25:40.083 --> 25:43.041
WE HAVE CONSENT
FROM THE PATIENTS INVOLVED

25:43.083 --> 25:45.041
TO REVIEW THEM, SO--
(Charlotte)
I'LL CALL OUR LAWYERS.

25:45.083 --> 25:47.458
IT'S NOT GONNA MATTER.
I CAN DEAL WITH THIS.

25:47.500 --> 25:51.041
(Charlotte) UNFORTUNATELY, THIS
ISN'T JUST ABOUT YOU ANYMORE.

25:51.083 --> 25:53.041
WE CANNOT LET THEM
WALK ALL OVER VIOLET.

25:53.083 --> 25:55.041
WELL, THEY'RE ALREADY
STANDING ON HER NECK,

25:55.083 --> 25:57.125
AND THEY SEEM HELL-BENT
ON MAKING THE REST OF US

25:57.166 --> 26:00.250
LAY DOWN, TOO.
THAT'S WHY WE NEED
TO MITIGATE THE DAMAGES.

26:00.291 --> 26:02.583
MITIGATE?
WELL, MAYBE IF VIOLET
WERE TO TAKE

26:02.625 --> 26:05.041
A VOLUNTARY LEAVE OF ABSENCE
UNTIL THE INVESTIGATION

26:05.083 --> 26:07.917
IS COMPLETE...
THAT'S YOUR IDEA
OF DOING SOMETHING?

26:07.959 --> 26:10.041
(Naomi) WELL, HE'S RIGHT.
SORRY I'M LATE.

26:10.083 --> 26:11.792
WHERE'S VIOLET?

26:11.834 --> 26:14.083
WE ASKED HER NOT TO COME.
IS THAT FAIR?

26:14.125 --> 26:18.375
RIGHT NOW FAIR IS NOT
OUR BIGGEST PROBLEM.
(Naomi) MAYBE IF WE SHOW THEM
THAT WE ARE COOPERATING--

26:18.417 --> 26:21.041
NO, IT'S NOT FAIR,
AND WE ARE COOPERATING.
IF VIOLET STEPS BACK,
IT MAKES IT

26:21.083 --> 26:23.875
LOOK LIKE SHE KNOWS
THAT SHE DID SOMETHING WRONG.

26:23.917 --> 26:27.041
OR IT MAKES IT LOOK LIKE
SHE'S TAKING IT SERIOUSLY.
OUR PRIMARY CONCERN RIGHT NOW
HAS TO BE

26:27.083 --> 26:30.041
PROTECTING THE PRACTICE. I MEAN,
THEY'RE COPYING OUR FILES,

26:30.083 --> 26:32.125
THEY'RE DRAGGING US DOWN
FOR INTERVIEWS.

26:32.166 --> 26:34.750
THIS INVESTIGATION
IS ONLY GONNA GET BIGGER.
(Amelia) LET THEM SEE
WHATEVER THEY WANT TO SEE.

26:34.792 --> 26:37.834
WE'RE NOT AN ORGANIZED
CRIME FAMILY. WE'RE DOCTORS.

26:37.875 --> 26:42.041
NO OFFENSE, BUT HOW LONG HAVE
YOU BEEN HERE, LIKE A WEEK?
(Charlotte) SHE'S NOT SUPPOSED
TO TAKE OFFENSE TO THAT?

26:42.083 --> 26:44.875
(Sam) LOOK--
LISTEN, WE ALL
TALK ABOUT OUR PATIENTS,

26:44.917 --> 26:47.458
NOT JUST VIOLET.
EXACTLY,
WHICH IS WHY WE DON'T WANT

26:47.500 --> 26:49.750
THE MEDICAL BOARD INVESTIGATING
ANYONE ELSE,

26:49.792 --> 26:52.125
SO WE--
THIS DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT.
ONE OF OUR OWN

26:52.166 --> 26:55.125
IS BEING ATTACKED.
WE NEED TO STAND BY HER.
ISN'T THAT WHAT THIS PLACE
IS SUPPOSED TO BE ABOUT?

26:55.166 --> 26:58.041
THE ONLY PEOPLE VIOLET TRIES
TO HELP MORE THAN HER PATIENTS

26:58.083 --> 27:00.041
ARE ALL OF US,
AND IF WE CAN'T...

27:00.083 --> 27:03.125
IF THIS IS ALL IT TAKES FOR US
TO TURN OUR BACK ON HER,

27:03.166 --> 27:06.291
THEN I...

27:06.333 --> 27:09.291
♪♪♪

27:15.375 --> 27:17.250
WHY DID YOU KEEP A FILE
ON PETE?

27:17.291 --> 27:19.041
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
HE WAS MY PATIENT.
FOR TWO MINUTES.

27:19.083 --> 27:21.041
YEAH, IT WAS--IT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO.

27:21.083 --> 27:24.375
WE HAD A FEW SESSIONS, THEN HE
CAME TO WORK FOR THE PRACTICE.
AND YOU SLEPT TOGETHER?

27:24.417 --> 27:26.041
WHY IS THIS RELEVANT?

27:26.083 --> 27:28.792
WELL, NOW HE'S MY HUSBAND.
WE HAVE A CHILD.

27:28.834 --> 27:31.792
THE FACT THAT YOU'RE MARRIED
HELPS, BUT I HAVE TO BE HONEST,

27:31.834 --> 27:33.959
THE SITUATION LOOKS BAD.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.959
PRIVILEGE REALLY DOESN'T SEEM
TO BE A SERIOUS MATTER AT O.W.G.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.959
OKAY, LOOK, WE ARE NOT
GONNA APOLOGIZE

27:39.000 --> 27:41.083
FOR THE WAY
WE PRACTICE MEDICINE.

27:41.125 --> 27:43.917
WE KNOW HOW TO HELP PEOPLE,
WE'RE GOOD AT IT.
I'M SURE YOU ARE,

27:43.959 --> 27:45.917
BUT THAT DOESN'T
GIVE YOU THE RIGHT

27:45.959 --> 27:48.834
TO SIT DOWN OVER COFFEE
AND DISCUSS SPECIFIC DETAILS

27:48.875 --> 27:50.834
OF PATIENTS YOU'RE TREATING
WITH OTHER DOCTORS

27:50.875 --> 27:53.041
JUST BECAUSE IT'S INTERESTING.
WELL, IT'S NOT GONNA CHANGE.

27:53.083 --> 27:56.208
I'M--I'M SORRY, BUT THE IDEA
THAT WE ARE SUDDENLY GONNA ACT

27:56.250 --> 27:58.208
LIKE A BUNCH OF DISCONNECTED
DOC-IN-THE-BOXES

27:58.250 --> 28:00.917
WHO SIMPLY SHARE SPACE--NO.

28:00.959 --> 28:04.208
I DON'T CARE WHO SUES ME
OR WHAT'S AT STAKE.

28:04.250 --> 28:07.625
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

28:07.667 --> 28:10.709
(people speaking indistinctly)

28:10.750 --> 28:12.959
(motor whirs)

28:13.000 --> 28:15.542
OH. I PREFER
YOU NOT BE HERE.

28:15.583 --> 28:18.375
THERE'S SOMETHING
I'D LIKE TO KNOW FIRST.

28:18.417 --> 28:20.667
I'M, UH...

28:20.709 --> 28:22.458
HAVING TROUBLE UNDERSTANDING

28:22.500 --> 28:24.458
WHY YOU WOULDN'T WANT
TO IMPROVE

28:24.500 --> 28:26.125
YOUR QUALITY OF LIFE.

28:26.166 --> 28:28.041
THE OTHER DOCTORS
AT THE PRACTICE

28:28.083 --> 28:30.041
SEEM TO THINK YOUR DEPRESSION
STEMS FROM GRIEF

28:30.083 --> 28:32.875
OVER THE LOSS
OF YOUR FRIEND WALTER.

28:32.917 --> 28:35.208
OH, AND YOU KNOW BETTER?

28:35.250 --> 28:37.333
I HAVE THAT WAY ABOUT ME,
DO I?

28:37.375 --> 28:39.333
(laughs) JEROME HAD
THE SAME BRASH CONFIDENCE.

28:39.375 --> 28:41.041
WH-WHEN YOU LOST HIM--

28:41.083 --> 28:44.041
I CAN'T IMAGINE SPENDING
HALF A CENTURY WITH SOMEONE

28:44.083 --> 28:47.041
AND THEN HAVING TO GO ON,
BUT YOU DID, FOR YEARS.

28:47.083 --> 28:49.041
AND ACCORDING TO DR. BENNETT,
YOU THRIVED,

28:49.083 --> 28:52.041
WHICH LEADS ME TO BELIEVE THAT
IF YOU CAN GET OVER JEROME,

28:52.083 --> 28:55.166
YOU CAN GET OVER WALTER, TOO.

28:55.208 --> 28:57.792
I NOTICED THE WORDS
ON THE GAME HAVEN'T CHANGED

28:57.834 --> 29:00.583
SINCE THE LAST TIME
I WAS HERE.

29:00.625 --> 29:04.041
WHO WAS IT YOU WERE PLAYING WITH
BEFORE YOU STOPPED?

29:04.083 --> 29:06.709
WALTER.

29:06.750 --> 29:08.792
HE WAS MY FRIEND.

29:08.834 --> 29:10.834
OH, WE TALKED...

29:10.875 --> 29:13.583
ABOUT OUR SPOUSES,
ABOUT OUR LIVES.

29:13.625 --> 29:16.834
WE BOTH LOVED TO PLAY SCRABBLE,
ALMOST EVERY DAY.

29:16.875 --> 29:18.458
THAT SOUNDS NICE.

29:18.500 --> 29:21.959
OH, IT WAS MORE THAN NICE.
IT WAS WONDERFUL.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.333
AFTER ALL THOSE YEARS
WITHOUT JEROME,

29:24.375 --> 29:26.667
TO HAVE SOMEONE
I CONNECTED WITH...

29:26.709 --> 29:28.500
THAT'S OKAY, MARION.

29:28.542 --> 29:30.834
BUT I-I COULDN'T.

29:30.875 --> 29:33.750
I COULDN'T DO THAT TO JEROME.
I JUST COULDN'T.

29:33.792 --> 29:35.333
YOU COULDN'T DO WHAT?

29:35.375 --> 29:36.959
(inhales deeply)

29:37.000 --> 29:39.959
WE WERE IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE GAME, THAT GAME,

29:40.000 --> 29:43.041
AND HE TURNED TO ME
AND SMILED AND HE...

29:43.083 --> 29:46.625
HE TOLD ME HE LOVED ME.

29:46.667 --> 29:49.291
WELL, WHAT DID YOU DO?

29:49.333 --> 29:51.458
(voice breaking)
I WAS SO EMBARRASSED.

29:51.500 --> 29:56.000
I... I TOLD HIM
TO GET OUT.

29:56.041 --> 29:58.041
A WEEK LATER, HE...

29:58.083 --> 30:00.166
HE WAS DEAD.

30:00.208 --> 30:02.041
BUT YOU DID LOVE HIM.

30:02.083 --> 30:03.375
(crying)

30:03.417 --> 30:06.041
OH, HOW COULD I TELL HIM?

30:06.083 --> 30:10.041
IT WAS LIKE
I WAS CHEATING ON JEROME.

30:10.083 --> 30:13.875
AND NOW
WALTER WILL NEVER KNOW.

30:13.917 --> 30:16.000
HE'LL NEVER KNOW
I LOVED HIM.

30:20.083 --> 30:23.375
HE SAT ACROSS THAT BOARD
FROM YOU FOR A LOT OF HOURS.

30:23.417 --> 30:25.917
RIGHT?

30:25.959 --> 30:27.709
SO HE KNOWS.

30:27.750 --> 30:30.083
WHETHER YOU SAID IT
OR NOT,

30:30.125 --> 30:33.375
I'M SURE HE KNOWS.

30:35.542 --> 30:37.125
(cries)

30:46.083 --> 30:49.417
WE ARE GOING TO BE SO LATE
TO COOPER'S DINNER.

30:49.458 --> 30:52.917
UM... WHY AREN'T YOU DRESSED?

30:52.959 --> 30:56.041
MAYBE SAM AND NAOMI
ARE RIGHT.

30:56.083 --> 30:58.625
MAYBE I AM PUTTING
THE PRACTICE AT RISK.

30:58.667 --> 31:01.625
NO, THEY'RE NOT RIGHT.
WELL, I COULD--
I COULD STEP AWAY.

31:01.667 --> 31:04.542
I MEAN, IF THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE
WANT, WHICH I DON'T KNOW,

31:04.583 --> 31:06.542
'CAUSE I WASN'T INVITED
TO THE MEETING,

31:06.583 --> 31:09.417
BUT IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES--
NO, LOOK,
YOUR BOOK WAS ALL ABOUT

31:09.458 --> 31:11.834
EXPOSING YOURSELF
TO HELP OTHER PEOPLE.

31:11.875 --> 31:14.625
YOU'VE STOOD UP TO EVERYTHING
THAT'S BEEN THROWN AT YOU,

31:14.667 --> 31:16.625
AND YOU'VE COME OUT
THE OTHER SIDE STILL STANDING.

31:16.667 --> 31:18.625
I DON'T SEE HOW TOMORROW'S
MEETING WITH THE BOARD

31:18.667 --> 31:20.041
IS GONNA BE ANY DIFFERENT.

31:20.083 --> 31:21.792
WIN/LOSE, RIGHT/WRONG,

31:21.834 --> 31:23.792
YOU'RE GONNA
COME THROUGH THIS STRONGER.

31:23.834 --> 31:26.625
THE ONLY MISTAKE I CAN SEE
IS NOT STANDING UP AT ALL.

31:26.667 --> 31:29.625
COME ON. GO GET DRESSED.
I CAN'T.

31:29.667 --> 31:32.667
(sighs) VIOLET,
IT'S A DINNER FOR COOPER.

31:32.709 --> 31:34.709
HE'S YOUR BEST FRIEND.
HE'S GETTING MARRIED TOMORROW.

31:34.750 --> 31:36.917
DON'T MAKE ME FEEL ANY WORSE
THAN I ALREADY DO.

31:36.959 --> 31:38.291
I JU--

31:38.333 --> 31:42.041
THE IDEA OF FACING
THOSE PEOPLE, I...

31:42.083 --> 31:43.709
I TEXTED COOPER,

31:43.750 --> 31:45.709
AND--AND--AND WHEN
YOU SEE HIM,

31:45.750 --> 31:49.041
JUST TELL HIM I LOVE HIM
AND I'M SORRY.

31:49.083 --> 31:51.417
(William Fitzsimmons'

31:51.458 --> 31:54.792
"The Winter From Her Leaving"
playing)

31:54.834 --> 31:59.041
(indistinct conversations)

31:59.083 --> 32:03.041
♪ SHOVE ME OUT TO SEE ♪

32:03.083 --> 32:05.291
♪ THE SEA ♪

32:05.333 --> 32:07.333
THE ONE MAID OF HONOR DUTY
CHARLOTTE GAVE ME,

32:07.375 --> 32:09.333
AND NOBODY
IS HAVING A GOOD TIME.

32:09.375 --> 32:11.333
YEAH, WELL,
THE MEETING THIS AFTERNOON

32:11.375 --> 32:14.041
DIDN'T EXACTLY LEAVE PEOPLE
IN A FESTIVE MOOD.

32:14.083 --> 32:17.041
I'M TELLING YOU, IF THE PARTY
WASN'T AT MY HOUSE,

32:17.083 --> 32:18.458
I WOULDN'T BE HERE.

32:18.500 --> 32:20.250
♪♪♪

32:20.291 --> 32:22.542
HEY.

32:22.583 --> 32:24.125
WHERE'S VIOLET?

32:24.166 --> 32:27.291
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO COME.
AND I DON'T REALLY BLAME HER.

32:27.333 --> 32:30.625
LOOK, I GET, OF COURSE, YOU
DIDN'T WANT TO LIE FOR VIOLET,

32:30.667 --> 32:33.041
BUT THE WAY YOU WERE TALKING
IN THAT MEETING--
PETE, IT WASN'T PERSONAL.

32:33.083 --> 32:36.750
YEAH, EXACTLY. IT WAS
SO COLD AND EMOTIONLESS.

32:36.792 --> 32:38.667
BUT SHE WROTE THE BOOK,

32:38.709 --> 32:41.041
OKAY, AND WHETHER YOU WANT
TO BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

32:41.083 --> 32:43.875
NOW WE HAVE A REALLY SERIOUS
SITUATION ON OUR HANDS,

32:43.917 --> 32:46.667
WHICH ISN'T GONNA GO AWAY.
SO WHAT, YOU JUST WANT
TO ABANDON VIOLET?

32:46.709 --> 32:48.041
NO, OF COURSE NOT, BUT...

32:48.083 --> 32:50.041
LOOK, IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU WANT TO BELIEVE--

32:50.083 --> 32:53.041
LOOK, IF EVERYBODY IN THIS DAMN
PRACTICE WANTS TO BE MAD AT ME,

32:53.083 --> 32:57.041
FINE. I AM STILL GONNA DO
WHAT I THINK IS RIGHT.

32:57.083 --> 32:58.875
♪♪♪

32:58.917 --> 33:01.041
FIRST OFF, THIS DOES NOT COUNT
AS STALKING.

33:01.083 --> 33:03.041
UH-HUH.
CHARLOTTE INVITED ME.

33:03.083 --> 33:05.458
AND ABOUT THE MARION THING--

33:05.500 --> 33:08.500
♪♪♪

33:12.709 --> 33:14.792
WHAT WAS THAT FOR?

33:14.834 --> 33:16.834
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

33:16.875 --> 33:19.208
(Sheldon)
YOU JUST NEVER KNOW.

33:19.250 --> 33:21.834
YOU KNOW, YOU THINK
YOU HIT IT OFF WITH SOMEONE,

33:21.875 --> 33:24.625
THAT MAYBE THEY'RE THE ONE--
I MEAN, YOU KNOW, THE ONE--

33:24.667 --> 33:26.208
AND THEN THERE'S...
(laughs)

33:26.250 --> 33:29.208
THERE'S JUST SO MANY WAYS
TO SCREW IT UP.

33:29.250 --> 33:31.834
BUT YOU--YOU KNOW WHAT?
BETTER SOONER THAN LATER.

33:31.875 --> 33:33.834
RIGHT? BECAUSE IF IT'S NOT
MEANT TO BE,

33:33.875 --> 33:36.041
THEN YOU'RE JUST
SETTING UP YOURSELF

33:36.083 --> 33:39.542
AND EVERYONE AROUND YOU
FOR A WHOLE LOT OF HEARTACHE.

33:39.583 --> 33:41.125
AM I MAKING ANY SENSE?

33:41.166 --> 33:44.208
ACTUALLY, A LOT.

33:44.250 --> 33:46.625
♪ THIS PEACE ♪

33:46.667 --> 33:49.583
YOU GUYS MUST BE
SO EXCITED ABOUT TOMORROW.

33:49.625 --> 33:52.000
VERY.
SHOULD BE A LOVELY DAY.

33:52.041 --> 33:54.375
(inhales)
LOOK, I CAN SPEND ALL NIGHT

33:54.417 --> 33:56.166
TRYING TO BACK IN
TO THIS CONVERSATION,

33:56.208 --> 33:59.250
BUT THE TRUTH IS, YOU GUYS
ARE WRONG ABOUT CHARLOTTE.

33:59.291 --> 34:03.041
I-IF YOU GOT TO KNOW HER,
IF YOU JUST GAVE HER A CHANCE...

34:03.083 --> 34:05.542
SHE DESERVES THAT,
DOESN'T SHE?

34:05.583 --> 34:09.000
♪♪♪

34:14.166 --> 34:16.041
THIS IS FUN.

34:16.083 --> 34:18.458
EXACTLY THE WAY I DREAMED IT
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

34:18.500 --> 34:20.500
ALL RIGHT,
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

34:20.542 --> 34:22.500
LET'S FIND MY PARENTS,
GET YOUR MOM.

34:22.542 --> 34:24.917
THE FIVE OF US WILL SIT DOWN,
AND WE'LL TALK THIS OUT.
COOPER.

34:24.959 --> 34:26.458
NO, DON'T ARGUE WITH ME.

34:26.500 --> 34:28.709
I MEAN, WE HAVE TO RESOLVE THIS
SO THAT TOMORROW,

34:28.750 --> 34:32.041
EVERYONE CAN BE HAPPY
AND RELAXED.
STOP TALKING AND TURN AROUND.

34:32.083 --> 34:34.291
(speaking indistinctly)

34:34.333 --> 34:37.000
MY FATHER IS NODDING HIS HEAD.
SO'S MY MAMA.

34:37.041 --> 34:39.041
WELL, HEY.

34:39.083 --> 34:41.834
GOOD TO SEE YOU
FINALLY TALKING.

34:41.875 --> 34:45.041
OH, LOOK,
WE'RE ALL PARENTS HERE.
YES, AND WE DO HAVE
THINGS IN COMMON.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.667
(chuckles) MAMA.

34:46.709 --> 34:49.083
WELL, WE DON'T WANT
OUR KIDS TO BE UNHAPPY.

34:49.125 --> 34:51.792
SO... WE AGREE.

34:51.834 --> 34:53.417
YOU HAVE
DIFFERENT RELIGIONS...

34:53.458 --> 34:55.834
AND YOU COME FROM
DIFFERENT CULTURES...

34:55.875 --> 34:58.125
AND YOUR PERSONALITIES...

34:58.166 --> 35:01.625
AND ALL OF THESE DIFFERENCES
DON'T MAKE FOR A HAPPY FUTURE.

35:01.667 --> 35:04.041
I THINK WHAT THE MOTHERS
ARE TRYING TO SAY IS,

35:04.083 --> 35:07.083
YOU TWO
SHOULDN'T GET MARRIED TOMORROW.

35:07.125 --> 35:10.125
♪♪♪

35:16.959 --> 35:20.667
WELL, THE JOKE IS THAT, UH,
DOCTORS MAKE THE WORST PATIENTS.

35:20.709 --> 35:23.041
UH, BUT--BUT FOR ME,

35:23.083 --> 35:25.208
UH, AFTER I STARTED TO HEAL,

35:25.250 --> 35:28.750
IT WASN'T LIKE I SAW
AN OPPORTUNITY OR ANYTHING.

35:28.792 --> 35:30.750
I JUST, UH, I STARTED WRITING,

35:30.792 --> 35:33.875
AND WHAT CAME OUT...

35:33.917 --> 35:37.041
IT WASN'T JUST THE STORY
OF ME GETTING THROUGH.

35:37.083 --> 35:41.500
I REALIZED THAT I WAS WRITING,
UH, HOW I GOT THROUGH--

35:41.542 --> 35:45.291
WHAT REALLY WORKED,
WHAT DIDN'T AND WHY.

35:45.333 --> 35:47.750
IT'S--IT'S NOT A ROAD MAP,

35:47.792 --> 35:50.041
BUT, UM, THIS BOOK IS ABOUT
MAKING THE LINK,

35:50.083 --> 35:52.917
NOT JUST BETWEEN
DOCTOR AND PATIENT,

35:52.959 --> 35:54.917
BUT PERSON TO PERSON.

35:54.959 --> 35:58.500
AND IT'S INTENDED TO BE, UM,
UH, PROOF, I GUESS,

35:58.542 --> 36:01.041
THAT IF YOU REALLY COMMIT
TO HELPING YOURSELF,

36:01.083 --> 36:03.709
NO MATTER
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH,

36:03.750 --> 36:05.709
THEN YOU CAN COME OUT
THE OTHER SIDE,

36:05.750 --> 36:11.291
STRONGER AND... HEALTHIER.

36:11.333 --> 36:13.500
DOES THAT MAKE ANY SENSE?

36:13.542 --> 36:17.041
I'M GOING TO ASK YOU
THE QUESTION AGAIN.

36:17.083 --> 36:18.834
DID YOU CONSIDER WHETHER,

36:18.875 --> 36:20.834
GIVEN THE NEWS COVERAGE
OF YOUR ATTACK,

36:20.875 --> 36:24.041
MS. KENT WOULD BE EASILY
IDENTIFIABLE IN YOUR BOOK?

36:24.083 --> 36:27.083
UM... HONESTLY, NO.

36:27.125 --> 36:30.083
DOES THE ISSUE OF
DOCTOR-PATIENT CONFIDENTIALITY

36:30.125 --> 36:32.083
CONCERN YOU GENERALLY?
COME ON, NEAL.

36:32.125 --> 36:34.750
OF COURSE IT DOES.
AN INVESTIGATION IS ONE THING,

36:34.792 --> 36:37.750
BUT TO IMPLY A COMPLETE LACK OF
PROFESSIONALISM BY DR. TURNER--
WE'RE CONCERNED ABOUT
A LACK OF PROFESSIONALISM

36:37.792 --> 36:39.125
AT OCEANSIDE WELLNESS
GENERALLY.

36:39.166 --> 36:42.250
AND IT MAY EXTEND
BEYOND DR. TURNER.

36:42.291 --> 36:44.250
BUT FOR THE TIME BEING,

36:44.291 --> 36:46.166
WE'RE CONCENTRATING
ON DR. TURNER,

36:46.208 --> 36:48.000
SPECIFICALLY THE SHARING

36:48.041 --> 36:50.583
OF POTENTIALLY
PRIVILEGED INFORMATION--

36:50.625 --> 36:53.667
IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU'VE ALREADY
DRAWN YOUR CONCLUSIONS--
I NEVER INTENDED TO DO
ANYTHING BUT HELP PEOPLE

36:53.709 --> 36:55.959
WITH THAT BOOK.
BOTH OF YOU, PLEASE.

36:56.000 --> 36:59.041
I THINK WE HAVE
ENOUGH INFORMATION

36:59.083 --> 37:01.041
TO MAKE A DECISION HERE.

37:01.083 --> 37:03.792
THE BOARD WILL BE IN TOUCH.

37:03.834 --> 37:05.375
(clicks pen)

37:05.417 --> 37:07.000
(rustles papers)

37:07.041 --> 37:10.000
(indistinct conversations)

37:46.083 --> 37:48.000
(sighs)

37:50.542 --> 37:53.000
(sighs)

38:10.083 --> 38:11.542
I THINK...

38:11.583 --> 38:15.041
I-I THINK IT'S A MISTAKE
FOR US TO DO THIS.

38:15.083 --> 38:17.709
EVERYONE OUT THERE,
THEY'RE MISERABLE.

38:17.750 --> 38:19.709
OUR PARENTS DON'T THINK
IT'S GONNA WORK,

38:19.750 --> 38:21.709
THE PRACTICE IS FALLING APART,
EVERYONE IS FIGHTING,

38:21.750 --> 38:24.375
AND I DON'T CARE WHAT ANYBODY
THINKS OR HOW THEY FEEL,

38:24.417 --> 38:26.375
NOT TODAY.

38:26.417 --> 38:29.250
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
ALL THAT MATTERS
IS YOU AND ME.

38:29.291 --> 38:31.250
AND THE REST OF 'EM?

38:31.291 --> 38:35.166
THEY DON'T HAVE TO AGREE
OR LIKE IT OR LIKE EACH OTHER,

38:35.208 --> 38:39.041
BECAUSE THIS IS NOT FOR THEM
OR ABOUT THEM.

38:39.083 --> 38:42.917
I AGREE, ONLY OUT THERE,
IT'S NOT JUST YOU AND ME.

38:42.959 --> 38:45.458
(Chrisette Michele's
"Love Is You" playing)

38:45.500 --> 38:48.583
I KNOW HOW TO MAKE THIS
FEEL RIGHT.

38:48.625 --> 38:52.959
♪♪♪

